subsequent investigations revealed that on the last day of world war i , between the beginning of the   armistice negotiations in the railroad cars encampment at the compiegne forest , french commander - in-chief marshal foch refused to accede to the german negotiators ' immediate request to declare a ceasefire or truce so that there would be no more useless waste of lives among the common soldiers .

